- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is relevant as the paper deals with communication links in networks.
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) could be relevant as BFS trees are commonly used in social network analysis.
- cs.AL (Algorithms) is a general category that could apply to this paper as it presents algorithms for maintaining BFS trees and single-source shortest paths.
